{"key":"processedPost-6658340","value":{"id":6658340,"first":6658317,"last":6659906,"when":1173641096,"utime":"03/11/07 10:24 PM","content":"Use your LC to inoculate sterilized quart jars of rye.  When they fully colonize, use them to spawn to the horse manure in a tray.  Make the substrate about 1 1/2\" thick at most.  Pans for some reason don't perform as well from a thick substrate.  When that fully colonizes, use 1/4\" of peat-verm for a casing layer.<br />RR","title":"Re: hpoo + pan.cyan basic questions","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}